column5: went out today managed to land quite the hog of a brown. 12lbs 6oz and about 2 hours later pulled in a smaller one too  two shots of the big boy      and the smaller fella
Hey yer zippers down.  Of all the fish I have caught,the brown is the most beautiful of colors in the fall.  TFS.
yep it sure is, had my camera in my sweatpants pocket  and i have to agree with you there, i love the colors they are a gorgeous fish
awsome fish, looks like a sweet spot with lots of elbow room lol.

They let you fish in the marina? Safe to say all the boats are removed and no one harassed you? That place is covered with signs saying no fishing..  Mind you I think Spiel and I hit it when it was froze over..  PS. Nice Browns!  G
boats have been out of the marina since the beginning of november and they take down the no fishing signs until spring when everything starts goin back in.

Guess I know why my SIGNS didnt work. they took down the signs at the beginning of november once all the boats were out lol
oh wow...what a beautiful fish. Nice work and sweet fishing spot.
thanks, theres the usual older fellas that are there day in and day out trying their luck for perch but other than that not too much foot traffic
what did you get them on roe or lures?
Awesome browns, especially the big male! I'm with you guys, I love the spawning colours on those males, and the big kype is cool as well. WTG
Very nice fish, love the colours!!!!
